rukus.text: Moses dictus to his servus ego non rest ego reach point ubi 2 rivers meet non matter quam long it takes
When they reached point ubi they met they forgot their fish it invenit its via back river sneakily
Post they passed ut point he dictus to his servus habet lunch totus hoc traveling thoroughly exhausted nos
He dictus Remember when nos sat rock back ibi Ego non paid attention to fish est devil factus me forget it it invenit its via back river strangely
Moses dictus est locus nos looking They traced their steps back
They invenit unus de noster servus nos beatus cum mercy, bestowed eum noster suus knowledge
Moses dictus to eum ego subsequentis vos ut vos teach me some de knowledge guidance bestowed upon vos
He dictus Vos non stand est me
Quam vos stand ut vos non comprehend
He dictus Vos invenit me DEUS testimentum patient Ego non disobey any command vos dedit me
He dictus vos subsequentis me tunc vos non ask me anything ego choose tell vos it
